<!-- MODULE 1: SCIENCE OF NERVES -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="module1">
  <div class="section-intro">
    <span class="module-tag">Module 01 · 15 mins · Badge: The Fearless Mind</span>
    <h2>The Science of Nerves</h2>
    <div class="meta">
      <span>🧠 Psychology</span>
      <span>💡 Reframe Technique</span>
      <span>🫁 Breathing Lab</span>
    </div>
  </div>
 
  <div class="module-section">
    <p class="theory-intro">Stage fright is not a weakness — it is your body's ancient survival system. Understanding <em>why</em> it happens gives you the power to control it.</p>
 
    <div class="theory-grid">
      <div class="theory-card">
        <div class="theory-icon">🧠</div>
        <div>
          <h4>The Amygdala Response</h4>
          <p>When you step in front of an audience, your brain's amygdala signals a "fight or flight" response — the same system that helped our ancestors survive danger. Your body does not know the difference between a lion and a live audience.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="theory-card">
        <div class="theory-icon">⚡</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Adrenaline Rush</h4>
          <p>Your body releases adrenaline, which increases your heart rate and makes you feel "wired." This is actually energy — the trick is directing it, not fighting it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="theory-card">
        <div class="theory-icon">🌫️</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Cortisol & "Brain Fog"</h4>
          <p>The stress hormone cortisol can cloud your thinking and make you forget your words. Controlled breathing before you speak directly reduces cortisol levels.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="theory-card">
        <div class="theory-icon">🫁</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Shallow Breathing</h4>
          <p>Anxiety causes you to breathe from your chest, not your diaphragm. This limits oxygen to the brain, making the fog worse. Deep breathing breaks this cycle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
 
    <div class="tip-highlight">
      <div class="tip-icon">✨</div>
      <div class="tip-text"><strong>The Reframe Technique:</strong> Instead of saying "I am nervous," say "I am excited." Physiologically, anxiety and excitement are nearly identical — the only difference is the mental label you give it. This simple switch has been proven to improve performance.</div>
    </div>
 
    <!-- LAB: BOX BREATHING -->
    <div class="section-divider"><span>Lab Exercise</span></div>
    <div class="lab-box">
      <h3>Box Breathing</h3>
      <p>Use this technique before any presentation or practice session. Breathe in a square: 4 seconds each phase. Complete 3 full rounds.</p>
      <div class="breathing-wrap">
        <div class="breath-ring" id="breathRing1">
          <div class="breath-inner">
            <div class="breath-phase" id="bPhase1">Ready</div>
            <div class="breath-count" id="bCount1">—</div>
            <div class="breath-timer" id="bTimer1">Press Start</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="breath-controls">
          <button class="btn-lab" id="breathBtn1" onclick="toggleBreathing1()">▶ Start</button>
          <button class="btn-lab secondary" onclick="resetBreathing1()">↺ Reset</button>
        </div>
        <div class="breath-cycles" id="breathCycles1">Cycles: 0 / 3</div>
      </div>
    </div>
 
    <!-- LAB: PHYSIOLOGICAL SIGH -->
    <div class="lab-box">
      <h3>The Physiological Sigh</h3>
      <p>This technique, used by neuroscientists, calms your nervous system in seconds. Follow the steps below:</p>
      <div class="lab-checklist" id="sighChecklist">
        <div class="check-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this, 'sigh')">
          <div class="check-box">✓</div>
          <span>Take a long, deep inhale through your nose (fill your lungs fully)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="check-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this, 'sigh')">
          <div class="check-box">✓</div>
          <span>At the top, take a quick second "sip" of air to fully expand the lungs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="check-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this, 'sigh')">
          <div class="check-box">✓</div>
          <span>Release with a long, slow exhale through your mouth (double the inhale length)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="check-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this, 'sigh')">
          <div class="check-box">✓</div>
          <span>Repeat 2–3 times. Notice the immediate sense of calm.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
 
    <!-- QUIZ 1 -->
    <div class="section-divider"><span>Knowledge Check</span></div>
    <div id="quiz1" class="quiz-wrap"></div>
 
